-- German Police Arrest Terror Suspect After al-Qaeda Video Threat, DPA Says
-- B y   A n g e l a   C u l l e n
-- 2010-11-05T12:41:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-05/german-police-arrest-terror-suspect-after-al-qaeda-video-threat-dpa-says.html
Police have arrested a suspected
terrorist in the western German town of Neunkirchen, Deutsche
Presse-Agentur reported, citing an unidentified police
spokesman.  The detention is tied to an al-Qaeda video threatening
attacks if a member of the so-called Sauerland terror group is
not set free, the news agency said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Angela Cullen at 
 acullen8@bloomberg.net  